Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion Shallot{1} into small pieces. Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Trim the @courgette{1} then slice into rounds about 1cm thick. Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{1}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all). Pop the lemon zest into a large #bowl{} with the @olive oil{1} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix, then add the @sea bass fillets{2} and coat in the lemony oil. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw fish.

== Bulgur ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the shallot and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Pour the @water{240%ml} for the bulgur wheat into the saucepan with the shallot and bring to the boil. Stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1} and @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Charred Courgettes ==

While the bulgur is soaking up the stock, pop a #frying pan{} on medium high heat (no oil!). Lay the courgettes in the pan in a single layer, season with a pinch of @salt{} and black pepper and cook them until charred, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side. Remove the courgettes from the pan and pop them in a bowl. Chop half the charred courgettes into small pieces. Cover with #foil{} but don't wash up the pan!

> Tip: If your pan is small, you may need to do this in batches.

== Lemony Dressing ==

While the courgette is cooking, pop the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} for the dressing into a small bowl with a squeeze of lemon juice and half the parsley. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix well and set aside.

== Sea Bass ==

Pop your frying pan back on medium high heat and, once hot, lay in the fish skin side down. Spoon any remaining lemon mixture over the fish. Cook until the skin is golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}, then turn over and cook for a further ~{2%minutes}.

> Tip: Don't move the fish while it's cooking skin side down or you won't get a crispy skin!

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== To Serve ==

When the bulgur has soaked up all the stock, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir through the tomatoes, chopped courgette, remaining parsley, and a small squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper add more lemon juice if you like things zesty. Spoon onto plates and top with the charred courgette slices and sea bass. Drizzle over the dressing and enjoy!